Package: sntmethods
Title: Analytical Methods for Sub-National Tailoring Workflows
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: c(
    person("Mohamed A.", "Yusuf",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "myusuf@appliedhealthanalytics.org",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-9339-4613",
                      second_email = "mohamedayusuf87@gmail.com")))
Author: Mohamed A. Yusuf [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Mohamed A. Yusuf <myusuf@appliedhealthanalytics.org>
Description: Provides core analytical functions for Sub-National Tailoring (SNT)
    processes, including incidence estimation, imputation of routine health data,
    campaign performance metrics, and small-area statistical methods. Designed as
    a companion to 'sntutils', this package focuses on epidemiologically grounded
    methods that produce reproducible, standardized outputs for malaria and related
    programmatic analyses.
